The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. Specifically, the paper focuses on sample complexity bounds for Q-learning with random walk exploration, which falls under the category of deep reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses structural properties of MDPs, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
